problem.markdown:
>> In a bidirectional RNN, assuming that the timeline of the sequence goes from left to right, the left-to-right RNN captures information coming from the ________ and the right-to-left RNN captures the information coming from the ______.<<

[[
future, past {{The left-to-right RNN cannot use information from the future, since it only has access to the information from previous timesteps. The right-to-left RNN cannot use information from the past, since it only has access to the information from future timesteps.}}
future, future {{The left-to-right RNN cannot use information from the future, since it only has access to the information from previous timesteps}}
past, past {{The right-to-left RNN cannot use information from the past, since it only has access to the information from future timesteps.}}
(past, future) {{A bidirectional RNN captures information from the past and the future.}}
]]
